ENTRY       EC 1.5.3.22                 Enzyme
NAME        coenzyme F420H2 oxidase;
            FprA
CLASS       Oxidoreductases;
            Acting on the CH-NH group of donors;
            With oxygen as acceptor
SYSNAME     reduced coenzyme F420:oxygen oxidoreductase
REACTION    2 reduced coenzyme F420 + O2 = 2 oxidized coenzyme F420 + 2 H2O [RN:R10602]
ALL_REAC    R10602
SUBSTRATE   reduced coenzyme F420 [CPD:C01080];
            O2 [CPD:C00007]
PRODUCT     oxidized coenzyme F420 [CPD:C00876];
            H2O [CPD:C00001]
COMMENT     The enzyme contains FMN and a binuclear iron center. The enzyme from the archaeon Methanothermobacter marburgensis is Si-face specific with respect to C-5 of coenzyme F420 [2].
